\section{Discussion}
Drawing from insights gathered through three action research cycles, we have distilled several lessons learned to enhance the effectiveness of sprint retrospectives, particularly in promoting active participation among team members and constructive criticism.

\subsubsection{Experiment with different retrospective formats}
Our findings support existing research \cite{Przybylek_2022_EMSE,Wawryk_Ng_2019} demonstrating that incorporating retrospective games enhances session dynamics and promotes active participation. Varying retrospective formats enables team members to reflect on the past from different perspectives, which
ensures that diverse perspectives are heard and considered.

\subsubsection{Monitor the effectiveness of different retrospective formats}
While \emph{Starfish} and \emph{Sailboat} were well-received, \emph{5L's} did not gain as much traction. This observation aligns with previous research findings and highlights the importance of monitoring team responses to different formats~\cite{Przybylek_2022_EMSE}. Mindfully selecting games that align with the team's specific context and maturity level is crucial for successful retrospectives.

